data.text:
At Rice:

2017: Conference USA Academic Honor Roll; Sidelined for the entire year with an injury… Worked hard to rejoin her teammates on the field and played in the Owls’ 2018 exhibition match against Spanish women’s professional league team CFF Maritim in the program’s international tour last March.

2016: Conference USA Academic Honor Roll; Played a strong second half of the season consisting of the key C-USA league matches... After playing just 43 minutes while appearing in two of the first six games, she then played in each of the ten C-USA regular season games with six starts... Also started on the backline in the opening round of the C-USA tournament in Charlotte... Played in 13 games overall with seven starts... Logged 847 minutes for the full season, but finished eighth on the squad with 714 minutes in C-USA games... Played 90 minutes in six of the last seven matches... Took a season-high three shots at Middle Tennessee... Maintained a .400 shots-on-goal percentage.

2015: Started the first eight matches of the season with an average of 81.6 minutes per match before being sidelined... Worked hard to rejoin her teammates, first as a reserve for the final five regular season matches before starting again in the opener of the the C-USA Tournament against Middle Tennessee... Contributed to five of the Owls' shutouts... Played a total of 853 minutes... Scored the game-tying goal against longtime state for SMU on the strength of a career-high seven shots... Scored on the road at Dayton.

Club: Versatile D/MF for Legacy SC. Served two years as team captain.

High School: A 2016 graduate of Hamilton High School in Chandler, Ariz.... Earned all-section and all-CUSD honors as a junior... Back-to-back team MVP... Serving third-straight season as the Huskies' team captain... Named East Valley Tribune All-State as a freshman... Team's defensive player of the year as a freshman in 2012... Outstanding student, who is a member of the National Honor Society... Social Studies Student of the Year... National Merit Scholar Semi-Finalist... AP Scholar with Distinction.

Personal: Full Name: Gabriella Rae Martinez. Parents: John and Sandy Martinez of Chandler, Arizona (one brother, one sister).
